otions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sayleth>Sayleth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/17/03 4:46:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm53.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=287>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bad news</span><hr size=1> Well, I have been submitting emails and such just about every day since starting this quest, reporting that it was broken, etc.  Got a response today from Alan VanCouvering.  Below is pasted from the bottom up the email of mine he responded to, his response, my response to his, and then his last response pertaining to the quest.  The formatting is very messed up as my OE often butchers text, and then cutting and pasting an email thread into EZboard doesnt work so well either.  If you dont want to read it all, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>the bottomline is that the Sage quests are done as of right now.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Sayleth<br>
<br>
edit: tried to clean up formatting some anyway<br>
<br>
----- Original Message -----<br>
From: &quot;VanCouvering, Alan&quot;<br>
To: &quot;'Olaf'&quot; &lt;olaf73@swbell.net&gt;<br>
Sent: January 17, 2003 4:27 PM<br>
Subject: RE: Quest Related Issues:: Fix please<br>
<br>
<br>
I'll pass your comments on to the team.  I'm sure they would love to extend these quest (and probably a few hundred others), and your suggestions are more than welcome.  But the quests are indeed complete as they are.<br>
<br>
I apologize for the trouble we've had getting them fixed.  We<br>
certainly didn't want to cause any frustration with the fixes that never were.  Sometimes these things are complicated to fix.<br>
<br>
Alan<br>
<br>
&gt; -----Original Message-----<br>
&gt; From: Olaf [mailto<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    laf73@swbell.net]<br>
&gt; Sent: Friday, January 17, 2003 2:23 PM<br>
&gt; To: VanCouvering, Alan<br>
&gt; Subject: Re: Quest Related Issues:: Fix please<br>
<br>
<br>
Thanks for the response finally, a lot of people have been banging their heads against a wall over this one for months now.<br>
<br>
Like I mentioned in the previous emails, its been 'fixed' 4 times and each time lots of people have been investing a great deal of time and plat into trying to figure it out, only to hit a brick wall again.  Thats very frustrating.  As to why myself and most other people think its still broken/incomplete, read on and I will do my best to explain.<br>
<br>
I will start by copying the entire quest text, then highlighting<br>
select quotes, and then conclude with my own observations and comments.<br>
<br>
Here is the complete text from the Sages:<br>
<br>
&lt;I snipped this for this post, its rehased on page 2 of this thread if you want to read it&gt;<br>
<br>
OK, now after reading all of that the first time through, this quest to me read like it was going to lead to an alternative method of obtaining 61+ spells.  It screams that, IMO.<br>
<br>
Quotes that stand out:<br>
<br>
Guynth--<br>
&quot;'It is my theory that all of the notes have been discovered, and creating new spells will just be a matter of combining notes in new and different fashions.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;For some reason I the extractor only works for spells between the 10th and 14th circles, I hope to have that problems resolved soon.&quot;<br>
<br>
Balic--<br>
&quot;'I have come to Knowledge to fine-tune my abilities in spell craft.  To date I've been able to create some minor incantations, but have had little success in creating any magic that was truly revolutionary. I am actually in a bit of a race with the other Sages who are my contemporaries. They too are looking to make a major breakthrough...&quot;<br>
<br>
Xelrin--<br>
&quot;'Greetings. I assume you are here to ask about my research? I imagine that word has spread of my groundbreaking approach to spell creation.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It is my conjecture that some of the magic may be extracted from these items in order to further our magical repertoire. Even in the case where an object has a spell that we already have access to, I believe the binding used to tie the magic to the object could be useful as well.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Each Sage mentions something along the lines of creation.  They also allude to the fact that right now (ie. pre-player intervention) the extractor box and their research is in its early stages.  Add to all of this the fact that this quest requires the research skill, a skill whose only application is the creation of spells, and a skill that has been abandoned since level 50 and the pre-Kunark days and I think you can see where this quest lead most players.<br>
<br>
Right now each Sage has 5 working combines that you can turn into them for very minor magic items, lore, with 5 charges each.  Or you can turn in a given Sages combine to one of their associates' assistants for some coin/gems (strictly sellables).<br>
<br>
Now, either the quest is incomplete, or its over...but can it really be over?<br>
<br>
I mean, this quest doesnt require a raid force or even a single group to acquire the components but its by no means easy.  It requires a *ton* of legwork, especially considering it had to be 'fixed' in 4 different patches in which lots of previously accomplished work had to be duplicated to rule things out.  Research has been abandoned so long, most int casters dont have it trained at all, let alone to the 150ish you need to make all of the quest combines trvial.  The components<br>
themselves are things that you might have a few in your bank...but not stuff that any one player is going to have all in their bank.  I mean, what reason would there be for a Necro to have Mage/Wizard research banked?  Or mid level spells other than their own?  Or items like an SSoY, or the bizarrely rare Kicsh Der Pavz?<br>
<br>
So I guess what I am saying is, given that the rewards are very nearly useless (the 5 charge stuff has low level effects that you simply are never going to use), and the fact that no one is gonna just have this stuff lying around, what would be the point in including this research based quest if it wasnt going to yield anything positive for the players doing it?<br>
<br>
I'd like to see some nice item come of this (This quest has been FAR more tedious and frustrating the Earring of the Solstice/PotC quest) or a method of gaining 61+ spells.  Perhaps the final reward could be a container that turned X amount of ethereals into a spectral, and X amount of spectrals into a Rune.  Or something along those lines.  Spells are still pretty damn scarce for most folks, especially 63+.<br>
<br>
Anyway, please, please follow up with me so that myself, and the rest of the folks working on this, can get some idea of where we stand on this quest.<br>
<br>
Sincerely<br>
Sayleth Soulblighter<br>
<br>
